summary: I move into college Monday. I’m a little nervous but it’s my dream school and I’m living in the city! Like downtown! It’s a...
question: I move into college Monday. I’m a little nervous but it’s my dream school and I’m living in the city! Like downtown! It’s a dream!! I bought really high fashion clothes and can’t wait to prance around with my coffee and my hair disheveled going from one interview to another (journalist gal)! Totally can picture running into H all crazy trying to get to my next interview and he’s like hey lmao
answer:
BUBBY I’M SO HAPPY AND EXCITED FOR YOU!!!

harry’d be the type to be fascinated with you, and he’s only seen you once which was right now, and he’d be genuinely intrigued with you prancing around — seeing you run pasy the café he’s in just as what he sees outside the window,.

would be confused as he sips his coffee yet wouldn’t be anymore as soon as you rushedly entered the cozy space he’s in, his position near by the entrance that in his attempt of opening the door for you, resulted with you colliding against his chest.

harry feels heat rise in his cheeks because all he had to fucking do was open a door and he managed to somehow trip over his feet, a messy and dopey smile on his face as you look at him.

“h-hey.”

tags: so im just making stuff up
body:
Harry Styles Imagine

A/N: Work with me here, I haven’t written in a while. Harry and Y/N are going to the beach, but Y/N feels insecure of her curves when the paparazzi catch her in her two piece. That was a terrible summary.


“Baaaaabe!! Are you ready?!” You chuckled at your cheeky boyfriend. You were going to the beach with Harry today, but you were stuck between two bathing suits, a light blue two piece or a solid purple one piece. You were about to pull your hair out with your indecisiveness when Harry came in the bedroom to find out what was taking you so long. “What’s the matter, love?” “Harry, which one should I wear?” He wrapped his arms around your waist and peered over your shoulder to glance down at the bathing suits sprawled across the bed. “The two piece, I love when you wear two pieces.” You looked at the two piece, but a voice in the back of your head made you doubt his decision.


“I haven’t actually worn that in a while, it’s a bit old.” “It would look beautiful on you, anything would.” After thinking about it again, you finally slip on the two piece and soon enough you’re on your way to the beach. You both ran out of the car, and hand in hand, you ran to the shore like children. He suddenly picked you up and carried you into the water. “Harry, no! The water is cold.” But it was already too late. He ran in the water until it was at his waist and dropped you right in. As soon as you came up, you made a scissor shape with your hand. “What’re the scissors for?” “It’s so when I catch you I can CUT ALL YOUR HAIR!” “NOO MY HAAIIIRRR!!” He laughed, dimples showing as he ran away from you. After hours of splashing around, you two decide to take a stroll on the boardwalk to the pier so you could watch the sunset.


“Look! It’s Harry and Y/N!” You both turned around and saw a small group of paparazzi speed walk towards you. “Just ignore them, love.” Your heart started racing when you remembered the real reason you didn’t want to wear your two piece. “Harry, are you gonna propose?” You took deep breaths, trying to get all the bad thoughts out of your head. “Y/N?” Harry felt your hand tense up in his. “Y/N, has he ever cheated?” You tried to focus on the sound of Harry’s voice. “Are you okay?”, he asked, turning to you. The world was spinning, but still you tried to push through. “Harry, did you write Medicine about Y/N?” You just had to breathe, everything is alright, everything is- “It looks like she needs a new swimsuit, it really isn’t holding in any of her fat in.” The pain you felt in your heart was like being struck by lightning. You started running towards the pier, blocking out your boyfriend calling your name. “Y/N, come back!”


It took every fiber of Harry’s being not to cuss that photographer out, but he knew that being there for you was more important. You made it to the pier, clutching your sides, tears streaming down your face. You couldn’t focus, your head filling with words of hatred. Ugly. Stupid. Fat. You closed your eyes and sat down on the ground. You just wanted the pain to stop. You would have stayed there forever if it weren’t for Harry ghosting his hand over your arm. “Y/N, nothing they say is important.” You lifted your head out of your self made shell. “I lied okay?! This bathing suit is brand new, I bought it so you would think I’m sexy but I didn’t want to wear it because it would show my stupid, ugly love handles and my fat waist and that photographer was very mean but he was right! Why do you even like me?! You have so many other options to choose from like models or physically fit girls that have like a six pack or something and they-” “They will never be you.” You looked at him for the first time during your rant, and you noticed a deep look in his green eyes, tears threatening to make their way out. “No one will ever compare to you. Every curve on your body is beautiful and whoever can’t see that should be nowhere near me because I will not stop telling the world how amazing you are. I love you, Y/N, and everything, everything about you. I want you to see everything I see, because the view is stunning.” “As stunning as the sunset we just missed?” A smile crept onto your face, all the anxiety slowly leaving your body. “Waaaaay better.” He leaned down and put his lips on yours, his kiss full of meaning and passion. The kiss was about to escalate, but you suddenly stopped. “What about the paparazzi guy?” “Oh he’s gone. Apparently one of those other photographers was his girlfriend, and she was not pleased with what he said. Then everyone else started taking photos her cussing him out.” You chuckled. “I love karma!”, you said as you leaned in to meet Harry’s lips once again.




A/N:

This this was absolutely garbage until halfway through, then it was slightly less garbage, but I did it

Also, if you feel as though nobody loves you because of the shape, size or skin you are in, you’re wrong, cuz I do, and you should too


Self care does not equal being selfish, so take care of yourself ❤️❤️


This authors note is probably better than the actual imagine, but it’s okay because I said so

You both ran out of the car, and hand in hand, you ran to the shore like children. He suddenly picked you up and carried you into the water. “Harry, no! The water is cold.” But it was already too late. He ran in the water until it was at his waist and dropped you right in. As soon as you came up, you made a scissor shape with your hand. “What’re the scissors for?” “It’s so when I catch you I can CUT ALL YOUR HAIR!” “NOO MY HAAIIIRRR!!” He laughed, dimples showing as he ran away from you. After hours of splashing around, you two decide to take a stroll on the boardwalk to the pier so you could watch the sunset.


“Look! It’s Harry and Y/N!” You both turned around and saw a small group of paparazzi speed walk towards you. “Just ignore them, love.” Your heart started racing when you remembered the real reason you didn’t want to wear your two piece. “Harry, are you gonna propose?” You took deep breaths, trying to get all the bad thoughts out of your head. “Y/N?” Harry felt your hand tense up in his. “Y/N, has he ever cheated?” You tried to focus on the sound of Harry’s voice. “Are you okay?”, he asked, turning to you. The world was spinning, but still you tried to push through. “Harry, did you write Medicine about Y/N?” You just had to breathe, everything is alright, everything is- “It looks like she needs a new swimsuit, it really isn’t holding in any of her fat in.” The pain you felt in your heart was like being struck by lightning. You started running towards the pier, blocking out your boyfriend calling your name. “Y/N, come back!”


It took every fiber of Harry’s being not to cuss that photographer out, but he knew that being there for you was more important. You made it to the pier, clutching your sides, tears streaming down your face. You couldn’t focus, your head filling with words of hatred. Ugly. Stupid. Fat. You closed your eyes and sat down on the ground. You just wanted the pain to stop. You would have stayed there forever if it weren’t for Harry ghosting his hand over your arm. “Y/N, nothing they say is important.” You lifted your head out of your self made shell. “I lied okay?! This bathing suit is brand new, I bought it so you would think I’m sexy but I didn’t want to wear it because it would show my stupid, ugly love handles and my fat waist and that photographer was very mean but he was right! Why do you even like me?! You have so many other options to choose from like models or physically fit girls that have like a six pack or something and they-” “They will never be you.” You looked at him for the first time during your rant, and you noticed a deep look in his green eyes, tears threatening to make their way out. “No one will ever compare to you. Every curve on your body is beautiful and whoever can’t see that should be nowhere near me because I will not stop telling the world how amazing you are. I love you, Y/N, and everything, everything about you. I want you to see everything I see, because the view is stunning.” “As stunning as the sunset we just missed?” A smile crept onto your face, all the anxiety slowly leaving your body. “Waaaaay better.” He leaned down and put his lips on yours, his kiss full of meaning and passion. The kiss was about to escalate, but you suddenly stopped. “What about the paparazzi guy?” “Oh he’s gone. Apparently one of those other photographers was his girlfriend, and she was not pleased with what he said. Then everyone else started taking photos her cussing him out.” You chuckled. “I love karma!”, you said as you leaned in to meet Harry’s lips once again.




A/N:

This this was absolutely garbage until halfway through, then it was slightly less garbage, but I did it

Also, if you feel as though nobody loves you because of the shape, size or skin you are in, you’re wrong, cuz I do, and you should too


Self care does not equal being selfish, so take care of yourself ❤️❤️


This authors note is probably better than the actual imagine, but it’s okay because I said so
